text: Claire Windsor (14 April 1892 - 24 October 1972) was an American actress who acted primarily in movies in the silent era. Her career lasted close to 27 years, although she made many very notable movies in her career. Windsor was born in Marvin, Kansas. She died of a heart attack in Los Angeles, California at age 80.
